Reasoning: The paper deals with game theory and optimization in simultaneous auctions, which are topics that fall under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science). The use of probabilistic price predictions and the concept of self-confirming prices suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The practical procedures for computing optimal bids and self-confirming price predictions may involve algorithms and data structures, which could place the paper under the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the empirical game-theoretic analysis suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of cs.EC (Economics and Computation).
